    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="102"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1546a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-16T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6912. What action did Socialist Conference take respecting British participation
                    in Stockholm conference in case Germany is represented, also in case Germany not
                    represented? Department desires copy of secret proposal reported submitted by
                        <persName corresp="#p_TA1">Thomas</persName> to British Labor Party and
                    Socialist Conference. Cable substance of this proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
